{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-20T13:49:42.019Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Turn-taking and alternation"},{"type":"text","text":" refers to the structured pattern of "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"who speaks next and when"},{"type":"text","text":" in a conversation. At its core, it's the practice where participants speak one at a time in alternating turns, with one person talking while others listen, then transitioning to the next speaker."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This back-and-forth exchange is fundamental to effective communication and ensures everyone has an opportunity to contribute to the conversation."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Core Concepts"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Turn"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"turn"},{"type":"text","text":" is a single unit of speech spoken by one participant before another participant takes the floor."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In AI chat models, each message (user or assistant) represents a turn."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Alternation"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Alternation"},{"type":"text","text":" is the fundamental rhythm where speakers alternate who has the \"floor\":"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Speaker A talks → Speaker B listens"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Speaker B talks → Speaker A listens"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"And so on"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This rhythm ensures seamless interaction and is essential for creating effective conversations."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3. Transition Relevance Place (TRP)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"transition relevance place"},{"type":"text","text":" is a point in the conversation where a turn may change—where the current speaker might stop and another might begin."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In human conversation, TRPs are signaled by:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pauses"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Eye contact"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Body language"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Intonation"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In AI conversations, TRPs are typically marked by:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The end of a message"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The user pressing \"Send\""}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The model completing its response"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"4. Adjacency Pairs"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Adjacency pairs"},{"type":"text","text":" are fundamental units of conversation that follow a predictable pattern:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Question → Answer"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Greeting → Response"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Request → Acceptance/Refusal"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"These pairs usually follow directly with no interruption."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Examples:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"User: \"What's the weather today?\"\nAI: [Provides answer]\n\nUser: \"Hello!\"\nAI: \"Hi! How can I help you?\"\n\nUser: \"Can you summarize this document?\"\nAI: [Provides summary]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"5. Preference Structure"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Adjacency pairs represent social actions, and not all second parts are equal. Some are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"preferred"},{"type":"text","text":" (structurally expected) and some are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"dispreferred"},{"type":"text","text":" (structurally unexpected)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Preferred responses:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Acceptance (to an invitation)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Agreement (to an assessment)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Acceptance (to an offer)"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Dispreferred responses:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Refusal (to an invitation)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Disagreement (to an assessment)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Decline (to an offer)"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How to do a dispreferred second:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Delay/hesitate (pause; \"er\"; \"em\"; \"ah\")"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Preface (\"well\"; \"oh\")"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Express doubt (\"I'm not sure\"; \"I don't know\")"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Token \"yes\" (\"that's great; I'd love to...\")"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Apology (\"I'm sorry; what a pity\")"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Turn-Taking in Human vs AI Conversations"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Human conversation"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In human conversation, turn-taking relies on:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cues"},{"type":"text","text":": Pauses, eye contact, body language, intonation to signal readiness to speak or willingness to yield the floor"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Rapid exchange"},{"type":"text","text":": The core niche for language use is in verbal interaction, involving rapid exchange of turns at talking"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Overlap"},{"type":"text","text":": Overlapping speech, simultaneous speech, and backchannels (backchannel signals) are common"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"AI conversation"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In AI chat models (like Claude via the Messages API), turn-taking is:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Discrete"},{"type":"text","text":": One message at a time, no overlap"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Explicit"},{"type":"text","text":": User presses \"Send\" or API calls the endpoint"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sequential"},{"type":"text","text":": Each turn is clearly labeled as "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"user"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"assistant"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Context-building"},{"type":"text","text":": The model sees the full conversation history with all prior turns"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Turn-Taking in Chat Models"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Message roles and alternation"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In chat models, you structure prompts using "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"three message roles"},{"type":"text","text":" that alternate:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":"left"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Role"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":"left"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Purpose"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":"left"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"User"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Questions, prompts, commands from the human"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Summarize this document\""}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Assistant"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Model's response to user inputs"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Here's the summary...\""}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"System"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High-level instructions, behavioral policies"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"You are a senior engineer\""}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Standard chat flow:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"What's the weather today?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"It's sunny with a temperature of 25°C.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"Will it rain tomorrow?\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This shows the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"alternating pattern"},{"type":"text","text":": user → assistant → user."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Turn-taking patterns"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pattern 1: Question-Answer (Adjacency Pair)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"User: \"What is prompting in Claude?\"\nAI: [Provides answer]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is a classic adjacency pair: question → answer."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pattern 2: Request-Response"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"User: \"Can you explain LLMs to me?\"\nAI: \"An LLM (Large Language Model) is...\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Request → Response is another adjacency pair."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pattern 3: Greeting-Response"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"User: \"Hello!\""},{"type":"hardBreak","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"AI: \"Hi! How can I help you today?\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Greeting → Response is a basic adjacency pair."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pattern 4: Multi-Turn Refinement"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Turn 1:\nUser: \"Write a blog post about urban planning and AI.\"\nAI: [Provides draft]\n\nTurn 2:\nUser: \"Make the opening more direct.\"\nAI: [Updates opening]\n\nTurn 3:\nUser: \"Use shorter sentences in the technical section.\"\nAI: [Simplifies]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each turn builds on the previous one, allowing progressive refinement."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pattern 5: Insertion Sequence (Extended Adjacency Pair)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"insertion sequence"},{"type":"text","text":" is when additional questions are inserted between the first and second parts of an adjacency pair:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"User: \"Can you help me with this code?\"\nAI: \"What's the issue?\"\nUser: \"I'm getting a TypeError.\"\nAI: \"Can you show me the error message?\"\nUser: \"TypeError: undefined is not a function.\"\nAI: [Provides solution]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The original question/request is answered only after a sequence of clarification questions."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why Turn-Taking Matters in Prompt Design"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Context Management"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Turn-by-turn alternation allows the model to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"maintain context"},{"type":"text","text":" by including past assistant messages in the dialogue history."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"Hello, Claude.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"Hi! I'm Claude. How can I help you?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"Can you explain LLMs to me?\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The model references the prior assistant message to provide context-aware responses."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Progressive Refinement"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Turn-taking enables "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"iterative back-and-forth exchanges"},{"type":"text","text":" to progressively build, refine, and improve model output through dialogue."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each response shapes the next turn:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ask for a summary → Then: \"Give me examples\" → Then: \"Now explain it to a 10-year-old\""}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each turn builds on the previous one"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3. Conversation Flow Control"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You can control turn-taking by:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Explicitly asking for confirmation"},{"type":"text","text":": \"Wait for my feedback before proceeding\""}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Stopping the AI"},{"type":"text","text":": End your turn with a question or instruction that requires a response"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prefilling assistant messages"},{"type":"text","text":": \"The answer is (\" to guide the model's response"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"4. State Tracking"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Managing a multi-turn conversation requires the AI system to track:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What has been established"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What has been promised"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What has been decided in earlier turns"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"state-tracking problem"},{"type":"text","text":" in multi-turn conversations."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best Practices for Turn-Taking in AI"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Use clear turn boundaries"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"End each user turn with a clear instruction or question that signals the turn is complete and a response is expected."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Good:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Summarize this document in 3 bullet points.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Less clear:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Summarize this. I think it's about AI in urban planning.\""}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Leverage insertion sequences"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"When you need clarification, use questions to insert a sequence before the main task:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"User: \"Can you help me debug this code?\"\nAI: \"What's the error you're getting?\"\nUser: \"TypeError: undefined is not a function.\"\nAI: [Provides debugging steps]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3. Explicitly control when the AI should stop"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use phrases like:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Wait for my feedback\""}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Stop after step 1\""}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Ask me before proceeding to step 2\""}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This prevents the AI from doing too much in a single turn."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"4. Use assistant pre-fills to guide turn-taking"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"On supported models, you can provide a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"prefilled assistant message"},{"type":"text","text":" to shape Claude's response:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"role\": \"assistant\",\n  \"content\": \"The answer is (\"\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This \"puts words in Claude's mouth\" to guide multiple-choice answers and control the turn's structure."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"5. Build conversation history intentionally"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Include prior turns that provide context for the current task:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"Hello, Claude.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"Hi! How can I help you?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"I need help with a Python function.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"Sure! What's the issue with the function?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"It's throwing a TypeError.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The model sees the full history and can provide context-aware debugging."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Turn-taking and alternation"},{"type":"text","text":" is the structured pattern of:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Who speaks next"},{"type":"text","text":" (user or assistant)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When"},{"type":"text","text":" (marked by transition relevance places like pauses or message ends)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How"},{"type":"text","text":" (through adjacency pairs like question-answer, request-response)"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In AI chat models:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Turns are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"discrete"},{"type":"text","text":" (one message at a time)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Roles "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"alternate"},{"type":"text","text":" (user → assistant → user)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Full history is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"visible"},{"type":"text","text":" to the model"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Turn-taking enables "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"progressive refinement"},{"type":"text","text":" through dialogue"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key concepts:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Turn"},{"type":"text","text":": Single unit of speech by one participant"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Alternation"},{"type":"text","text":": Speaker A talks → Speaker B listens → Speaker B talks → Speaker A listens"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"TRP"},{"type":"text","text":": Transition Relevance Place (where turn may change)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Adjacency pairs"},{"type":"text","text":": Question → Answer, Greeting → Response, Request → Response"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Preference structure"},{"type":"text","text":": Some responses are expected (preferred), some are unexpected (dispreferred)"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Turn-taking is fundamental to effective AI conversations and enables context management, iterative refinement, and state tracking across multiple turns."}]}]}}
